  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package contains the W-CON-01 weakness: the decision record outcome is Accepted despite several CredibilityFactors carrying neither requiredLevel nor achievedLevel, meaning the acceptance decision is not grounded in complete structured factor evidence.",
